[thinking] 
[thinking] I'm questioning whether the naming conventions for test classes, especially for inner or anonymous classes, could lead to violations. For instance, I see that a nested DTO could create a class name like DTOTest$BundleInfoDTO, which may not be ideal. 
[thinking] 
[thinking] I wonder if using package-private top-level classes could work instead. There’s the thought of one public top-level class while maintaining a direct mapping between dynamic-access report classes and test files, possibly allowing a helper class. It’s a bit of a puzzle.
